# Content Rules

This project is a personal engineering blog at sujeet.pro. When working with content files, follow these guidelines.

## Guidelines

Read the full guidelines before creating or editing content:

- `ai-guidelines/README.md` — task routing and validation commands
- `ai-guidelines/content-structure.md` — content model, audience, frontmatter, citations
- `ai-guidelines/markdown.md` — local markdown rules layered on top of Pagesmith
- `ai-guidelines/diagrams.md` — diagram expectations, file layout, embedding
- `ai-guidelines/packages.md` — Pagesmith and diagramkit reference map
- `ai-guidelines/workflows/article-workflow.md` — article create/update/review
- `ai-guidelines/workflows/blog-workflow.md` — blog create/update/review
- `ai-guidelines/workflows/update-docs.md` — AI doc refresh workflow

Prefer repo-local skills when they match the task:

- `sp-article`
- `sp-blog`
- `sp-sync`

Before editing content, identify the companion metadata that may need to change with it:

- `content/articles/meta.json5`
- `content/blogs/meta.json5`
- `content/home.json5`
- `content/redirects.json5`

## Quick Reference

### Frontmatter (required for all content)

```yaml
---
title: "Title"
description: "One-line description"
publishedDate: 2026-03-15
lastUpdatedOn: 2026-03-20
tags: [topic-a, topic-b]
---
```

Do NOT set `layout` or `category` — resolved from `meta.json5`.

### Content Types

- Articles: `content/articles/<slug>/README.md` — research-backed, staff-level, diagram-heavy
- Blogs: `content/blogs/<slug>/README.md` — shorter, personal, still technically correct
- Projects: legacy only for now; do not create new project content unless explicitly asked

### Diagrams

Write source files (`.mermaid`, `.excalidraw`, `.drawio`, `.dot`) in `<slug>/diagrams/`. Never generate SVG directly. Run `npm run diagrams` to render.

Preferred reference pattern:

```html
<figure>
  <img class="only-light" src="./diagrams/name-light.svg" alt="Description" />
  <img class="only-dark" src="./diagrams/name-dark.svg" alt="Description" />
</figure>
```

### Validation

```bash
npm run validate         # Check schemas and cross-file references
npm run build            # Full build verification
vp check                 # Format + lint
```
